INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE

INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE—these are called CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete).
---
🧠 1. INSERT (Add Data)
👉 INSERT = Add new row (new record)
---
🔹 Basic Syntax
INSERT INTO table_name VALUES (value1, value2, value3);
---
🔹 Example
Table: students
id	name	age

Add Data:
INSERT INTO students VALUES (1, 'Rahul', 22);

👉 Now table becomes:
id	name	age
1	Rahul	22

---
🔹 Insert Specific Columns
INSERT INTO students (id, name) VALUES (2, 'Amit');
👉 age will be NULL
---
⚠️ Common Mistake
❌ Wrong:
INSERT INTO students VALUES ('Rahul', 22);
👉 Missing column → error

---
🔄 2. UPDATE (Modify Data)
👉 UPDATE = Change existing data

---
🔹 Basic Syntax
UPDATE table_name
SET column = value
WHERE condition;

---
🔹 Example
UPDATE students
SET age = 23
WHERE id = 1;

👉 Before:
id	name	age
1	Rahul	22

👉 After:
id	name	age
1	Rahul	23

---
🔹 Update Multiple Columns
UPDATE students
SET name = 'Rahul Sharma', age = 24
WHERE id = 1;
---
⚠️ VERY IMPORTANT (Interview + Real Life)
❌ Without WHERE:
UPDATE students SET age = 25;
👉 This updates ALL rows 😱

---
❌ 3. DELETE (Remove Data)
👉 DELETE = Remove row(s)
---
🔹 Basic Syntax
DELETE FROM table_name
WHERE condition;
---
🔹 Example
DELETE FROM students
WHERE id = 1;

👉 Row is deleted
---
⚠️ VERY IMPORTANT
❌ Without WHERE:
DELETE FROM students;
👉 Deletes ALL data 💀
---
🔥 Difference: DELETE vs TRUNCATE (Important)
Feature	              DELETE	             TRUNCATE
WHERE allowed	         ✅ Yes	              ❌ No
Delete specific rows	 ✅ Yes	              ❌ No
Speed.                 Slow.                Fast
Rollback	             Possible	            Not always

---
🧠 Real-Life Example
👉 Banking system:
Transfer money

UPDATE accounts SET balance = balance - 100 WHERE id = 1;
UPDATE accounts SET balance = balance + 100 WHERE id = 2;

---
🎯 Practice Questions
Try yourself:
1. Insert 3 students
2. Update age of one student
3. Delete one student
4. Update all students age to 30 (careful ⚠️)
5. Delete students where age < 20

--
💡 Final Summary
INSERT → Add new data
UPDATE → Modify existing data
DELETE → Remove data
---

🚀 Pro Tip (Very Important)
Before running UPDATE or DELETE: 👉 Always check with SELECT first
SELECT * FROM students WHERE id = 1;
